1
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,280
You're leaving just like that.

2
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,120
It's always like this.

3
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:28,579
You never tell me earlier.

4
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:30,600
Make sure you keep those US dollars safe.

5
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:31,760
Where are the US dollars in the safe?

6
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:32,620
I took them all.

7
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:34,079
When you get there,

8
00:03:34,079 --> 00:03:35,320
we'll keep in touch anytime.

9
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:37,160
Let me know you're safe when you arrive.

10
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:38,040
Call me anytime.

11
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:38,960
Fengnian.

12
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,160
Yunkui.

13
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:50,040
You're really alive.

14
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:57,560
I'm alive.

15
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:02,610
I heard from Yujiao.

16
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,660
I need to talk to Yunkui alone.

17
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:07,680
You go first,

18
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:09,680
and have them come back to pick me up.

19
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:10,720
Okay.

20
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:13,920
Yunkui.

21
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,960
It's good that you're alive.

22
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,600
It's good that you're alive.

23
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:18,720
I'll get going.

24
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:28,480
Here.

25
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:30,160
Ma'am, let me take it.

26
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:32,240
The commander told us to go first.

27
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,840
We'll arrange a car to pick him up later.

28
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:35,000
Yes.

29
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,440
Still alive.

30
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:57,800
Alive.

31
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:59,000
You're so bold.

32
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,480
You dare to return to Nanjing at this time.

33
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,680
Nanjing is tense right now.

34
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:04,160
There are military police and spies everywhere.

35
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:05,890
Sun Huaiyi's men are also here.

36
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:07,080
If anyone spots you,

37
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:08,000
it's a dead end.

38
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,020
I'm not afraid.

39
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:10,520
I'm waiting for him to arrest me.

40
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:12,650
I'm going to confront him face to face.

41
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:13,360
Confront?

42
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:15,360
Who are you confronting?

43
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:18,060
This is an extraordinary period.

44
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:18,480
You,

45
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,520
are a definite runaway general.

46
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,600
No need for a court-martial,

47
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:23,520
or a trial.

48
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:26,160
Sun Huaiyi can execute you anytime.

49
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,280
I don't get it.

50
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,160
I argued with him,

51
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:31,480
but does he hate me that much?

52
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:38,640
Sun Huaiyi's command was conservative.

53
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:40,840
The 187th Division suffered heavy losses.

54
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:43,370
Someone has to take responsibility for this.

55
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,040
If Sun Huaiyi takes it,

56
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:47,530
the 187th Division might be deactivated.

57
00:05:48,159 --> 00:05:49,620
If a subordinate takes it,

58
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:52,080
the 187th Division might regroup.

59
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:53,570
But at that time,

60
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:56,360
everyone thought you died for the country.

61
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:58,600
So Sun Huaiyi put the blame on you.

62
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,120
That must be it.

63
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,880
The runaway general is to blame.

64
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:11,040
Is that what you mean too?

65
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,560
Is it?

66
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,340
For a soldier on the battlefield,

67
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:23,890
what's the biggest insult?

68
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:28,160
A deserter.

69
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:33,400
Tell me,

70
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,640
am I a deserter?

71
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:38,080
Yunkui.

72
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:41,170
We've been brothers for so many years.

73
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,680
How do you think I see you?

74
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:52,000
On November 6th,

75
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,560
I went to Commander Luo.

76
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,360
I told him everything I knew.

77
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,600
He only answered me three words.

78
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,600
I know.

79
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,360
On November 8th,

80
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:02,360
I stopped Commander Chen in the dining hall.

81
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,160
Before I could even speak,

82
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:03,920
he said,

83
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:04,840
'Say no more.

84
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,560
I know what you are going to say.'

85
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,640
It's always the same.

86
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,200
Say no more. I know.

87
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,080
They know everything,

88
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,890
but no one wants to bring it out in the open.

89
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,840
Ultimately,

90
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,460
Sun Huaiyi didn't treat you as one of his own.

91
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:25,800
One of his own?

92
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,810
Were those 6,000 brothers not his own?

93
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:30,200
Did they just let them

94
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,130
become cannon fodder for nothing?

95
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,409
This is not over.

96
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:35,040
I will either go to Minister He,

97
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,360
or I will go to the Chairman.

98
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,159
Are you crazy?

99
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:38,400
Well,

100
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,800
Are we closer to the Chairman,

101
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,080
or is Sun Huaiyi

102
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:41,880
closer to him?

103
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:44,200
The Battle of Shanghai just ended.

104
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:46,560
The direct line troops lost seventy or eighty percent.

105
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,480
Nanjing needs to be defended.

106
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:48,840
China needs to be defended.

107
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:50,400
Those warlords need to be guarded against.

108
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,200
Would the Chairman clip his own wings at this time

109
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,800
and investigate Sun Huaiyi?

110
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,240
Think about it carefully.

111
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,560
You want justice?

112
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:58,400
You surviving

113
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,640
is the greatest justice.

114
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:03,840
With the enemy at the gates,

115
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:06,360
do we really need to argue about right and wrong?

116
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:07,520
Things will work out in time.

117
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:08,520
Work out?

118
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:10,120
Can you even cover up

119
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,680
the lies you told yourselves?

120
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,080
Where did the 159th Division go?

121
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:15,440
My brothers were defending Baijiazhai to the death!

122
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:16,160
If we joined forces,

123
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:18,240
we could have won that battle, you know?

124
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,040
And you?

125
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:19,640
You retreated at the last minute,

126
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:21,480
making my soldiers look like deserters.

127
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:22,600
Is that fair?

128
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:25,080
Is it?

129
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:27,640
What's the point of saying this now?

130
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:28,440
It has a point.

131
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:29,580
I'm asking you,

132
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,800
who gave the order to retreat from Liuzhen?

133
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:32,730
I can't tell you.

134
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:33,360
Answer me.

135
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,960
I can't tell you.

136
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,320
Yunkui,

137
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,370
I have a suggestion.

138
00:08:41,640 --> 00:08:42,700
I'll go find Dai Li.

139
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:43,970
I can talk to him.

140
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:45,360
If he helps,

141
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:48,400
he will speak up for you to the Chairman.

142
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,610
Then you will have a chance.

143
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,720
Sun Huaiyi is the best at seeing which way the wind blows.

144
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:53,720
When the time comes, he will naturally

145
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,980
help cover up your battlefield affairs.

146
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,090
At that time,

147
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,960
whether you want to mend your relationship with him

148
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:00,160
or get revenge on him,

149
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:01,560
it's up to you.

150
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,330
The old man and your wife

151
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:11,540
are probably almost in Wuhan.

152
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:12,920
I asked someone to get them three

153
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:14,180
boat tickets to Wuhan.

154
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,760
Thank you.

155
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,860
You know the old man's temper.

156
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,920
He was furious when he heard about your accident.

157
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:24,980
It took a lot to persuade him to leave.

158
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:26,000
Did my dad...

159
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:26,720
Alright,

160
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:27,520
stop talking.

161
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:30,220
Take these US dollars for now.

162
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:31,320
No.

163
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,760
Hurry to Wuhan

164
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,680
and meet up with your family.

165
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:39,880
With the clothes you are wearing,

166
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:41,720
you'll be caught as soon as you step out.

167
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,400
Come, go upstairs with me to change.

168
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,640
Can Nanjing be held?

169
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:52,610
What do you mean?

170
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:54,120
I know the rest of my division

171
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,120
was ordered to retreat to Mufu Mountain.

172
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,000
I can temporarily put aside

173
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,800
all my disputes with Sun Huaiyi.

174
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:00,360
I want to defend Nanjing.

175
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,800
It's not that simple.

176
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:03,320
You,

177
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,560
hurry and send a telegram to the old man

178
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:05,620
to say you're safe.

179
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,160
I'll go get it for you.

180
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,960
There! Stop!

181
00:11:42,280 --> 00:11:43,610
Stop looking, let's go.

182
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:51,320
Come with us.

183
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:29,720
Keep order.

184
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:30,360
Watch out.

185
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:31,040
Slow down.

186
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,240
Keep order.

187
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:34,080
Be safe.

188
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,360
Watch out for the kids.

189
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,120
Slow down.

190
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:38,240
Slow down.

191
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:40,320
Oh my goodness.

192
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:41,120
Watch out for the elderly and children.

193
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,680
Taking this boat is killing me.

194
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:43,240
Stop swaying, Mrs. Liu.

195
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:45,160
My legs don't feel like mine anymore.

196
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:45,720
I'm not swaying.

197
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:46,520
Stop swaying.

198
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,530
You're the one swaying, ma'am.

199
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:56,880
Quick, sit down.

200
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:00,920
How did Shanghai turn into this?

201
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,080
Master,

202
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:03,340
Shanghai is so big,

203
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,640
where are we heading?

204
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:07,200
No. 8 Jurenli, French Concession.

205
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:08,760
We have a house there,

206
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:09,800
understand?

207
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:13,800
Hello, excuse me,

208
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,840
how do we get to the French Concession?

209
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:17,000
Walk ahead for three miles,

210
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,560
and you'll reach the French Concession.

211
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,560
Thank you.

212
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:21,940
Let's go, three miles.

213
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:23,200
Wait,

214
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:25,180
Ma'am is not feeling well.

215
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,760
Wanfu, hurry and call a rickshaw.

216
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:28,700
Go quickly.

217
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:31,640
Slow down.

218
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:33,160
Slow down.

219
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:37,640
Go quickly.

220
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:40,280
Master, how do I call one?

221
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:41,640
Call one!

222
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:43,640
I yelled but they won't come.

223
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:45,760
Master.

224
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:47,800
Ma'am.

225
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:50,240
Slow down.

226
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:06,680
Go quickly.

227
00:14:12,360 --> 00:14:14,160
Master, come sit.

228
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:17,280
Master.

229
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:17,800
Dad.

230
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:18,960
Be careful.

231
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:37,400
Rickshaw! Rickshaw!

232
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:38,600
Let's go. To the pier.

233
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,040
I'm not taking passengers.

234
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:41,280
No, please, brother, help me out.

235
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:42,940
My wife is about to give birth.

236
00:14:43,160 --> 00:14:44,400
I'm in a hurry to pick someone up.

237
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:45,160
How about this.

238
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:46,760
I'll give you one dollar, okay?

239
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:47,440
One dollar?

240
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,120
You obviously don't know the market rate.

241
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,720
The starting fare is three dollars now.

242
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:51,480
Let go.

243
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:52,800
Little punk.

244
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:54,560
You're obsessed with money.

245
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,920
Why are you having a baby now?

246
00:14:55,920 --> 00:14:57,400
Tell your kid to wait a bit longer.

247
00:14:57,400 --> 00:15:00,000
You won't earn three dollars in your lifetime.

248
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:06,320
Make way.

249
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:08,920
Make way.

250
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:10,760
Make way.

251
00:15:23,360 --> 00:15:24,480
Thank you.

252
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:25,760
You're welcome.

253
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:32,800
Thank you.

254
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:34,360
You're welcome.

255
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,370
Stop! My cart! Stop!

256
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:06,800
The money is on the goods.

257
00:16:13,640 --> 00:16:14,840
What kind of person is this?

258
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:17,170
You should have told me you were buying it.

259
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:27,010
Where did you get this broken cart?

260
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:28,160
It's wobbling side to side.

261
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:29,690
It's like selling piglets.

262
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:32,160
Ma'am, I didn't mean it.

263
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:33,560
Sit tight.

264
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:35,880
If you think it's broken, go get one yourself.

265
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:37,560
I was almost beaten to death.

266
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:40,020
You didn't rent this cart?

267
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:41,320
Watch out for the bump!

268
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:42,160
Slow down.

269
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:43,440
Wait.

270
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:45,560
Did you say this cart was stolen?

271
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:47,490
How could I have stolen it, Master?

272
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:48,760
The money you gave me,

273
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:50,880
I spent it all on this cart.

274
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:53,880
Taking without asking is stealing.

275
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:55,880
I won't ride in this cart.

276
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:56,920
Slow down.

277
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:58,210
Ma'am, are you okay?

278
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:02,160
Master, look at the situation now.

279
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:04,060
The madam is pregnant.

280
00:17:04,119 --> 00:17:05,920
Having a broken cart is better than nothing.

281
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:06,560
Right?

282
00:17:06,839 --> 00:17:08,240
Get in quickly, let's go.

283
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:09,369
Then you ride it.

284
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:10,560
I can't ride it.

285
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:12,760
I can't sit on the same level as the madam.

286
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:13,560
Please get in.

287
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:14,440
You sit.

288
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:15,680
I won't.

289
00:17:16,079 --> 00:17:17,160
Please get in, let's go.

290
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:18,890
If he tells you to sit, just sit.

291
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:20,160
You are like a dead weight.

292
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,480
Why are you being so modest?

293
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:22,810
You're the dead weight.

294
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:24,119
Father.

295
00:17:25,079 --> 00:17:26,480
I'll walk with you.

296
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:28,200
Sitting is

297
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,930
more uncomfortable than walking.

298
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:32,600
Wanfu is also tired.

299
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,560
Alright.

300
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:37,680
Wanfu.

301
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:40,320
You must not steal.

302
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:41,160
I...

303
00:17:41,520 --> 00:17:42,180
Okay, okay.

304
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:44,760
A person of high ideals doesn't drink stolen water,

305
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:47,080
and an honest person doesn't accept food handed out in contempt.

306
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:48,940
This is a basic principle of life.

307
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:50,920
You are not a hired hand of our family,

308
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:51,960
nor a coolie.

309
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:54,080
I won't let you work for nothing.

310
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,360
After you drop us off

311
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:56,840
at the concession later,

312
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:58,600
I order you

313
00:17:58,920 --> 00:18:00,880
to return this cart.

314
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:04,040
Then I'll buy you a ticket to Wuhan.

315
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:06,880
From then on, we'll be even.

316
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:08,560
You're on your own.

317
00:18:08,840 --> 00:18:09,720
Fine.

318
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,000
We'll be even.

319
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:11,900
But Master,

320
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:13,800
remember what you just said.

321
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,120
Let's go.

322
00:18:18,360 --> 00:18:19,160
Be careful.

323
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:42,600
Let's go.

324
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:44,440
Go.

325
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,920
You also know fear when the house collapsed.

326
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:50,680
Your whole family are gentlemen,

327
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:51,810
and I'm the villain.

328
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:53,400
Since I'm such a villain helping you with your luggage,

329
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:55,600
carry it yourselves if you're capable.

330
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:57,440
Why are you rambling?

331
00:18:58,080 --> 00:18:59,410
Chengtuo, don't speak.

332
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:00,400
Rambling.

333
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:29,210
Don't get any ideas.

334
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:30,360
There are checkpoints outside.

335
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:31,080
If you dare to run,

336
00:19:31,080 --> 00:19:32,240
I'll shoot you.

337
00:20:57,120 --> 00:20:59,160
Get up.

338
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:03,920
Get up.

339
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:05,160
When will this gate open?

340
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:05,640
Do you know what China

341
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:06,640
is like right now?

342
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:08,740
It's useless telling me all this.

343
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:13,800
Grandpa.

344
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:15,120
Right here.

345
00:21:17,040 --> 00:21:17,840
We're here.

346
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:28,040
Be careful.

347
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:29,160
Excuse me,

348
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:30,600
coming through.

349
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:31,120
Thank you.

350
00:21:31,120 --> 00:21:32,580
Do you know how cruel it is?

351
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:37,120
Grandpa, let's go up front and see.

352
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:39,280
Madam, have a rest.

353
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:39,960
Let's go.

354
00:21:40,280 --> 00:21:41,560
Excuse me, coming through.

355
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:42,960
Thank you.

356
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:43,890
Coming through.

357
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:44,920
Grandpa, slow down.

358
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:45,880
Come, coming through.

359
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:47,560
The gate will open when it's supposed to.

360
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:49,840
If it doesn't open, staying here for a year won't help.

361
00:21:49,840 --> 00:21:51,480
Coming through. Mind the oil.

362
00:21:51,480 --> 00:21:52,600
Coming through. Thank you.

363
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:53,200
Thank you.

364
00:21:53,240 --> 00:21:54,240
Come on, Grandpa.

365
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:55,360
Officer,

366
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,680
we have a proper property

367
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,080
in the Concession.

368
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:00,720
No. 8, Jurenli.

369
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:01,280
We...

370
00:22:01,280 --> 00:22:02,560
Step back. Step back.

371
00:22:02,840 --> 00:22:03,880
I hear this

372
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:05,490
hundreds of times a day.

373
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,520
No, you misunderstood.

374
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:08,440
Look.

375
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:13,680
This is our title deed.

376
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,800
We are going back to our own home.

377
00:22:16,360 --> 00:22:18,000
Please open the gate and let us in.

378
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:18,880
If I let you in

379
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:20,320
just because you have a title deed,

380
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:21,520
there are over 500 people over there

381
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:22,240
who all have title deeds.

382
00:22:22,240 --> 00:22:22,520
This...

383
00:22:22,520 --> 00:22:24,240
Should I let them all in?

384
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:27,160
That... that's unreasonable.

385
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:28,240
Unreasonable?

386
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,920
This is the French Concession.

387
00:22:29,920 --> 00:22:31,050
They make the rules.

388
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:32,480
What?

389
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:33,960
What kind of logic is that?

390
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:34,560
Exactly.

391
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:36,840
Isn't this the tail wagging the dog?

392
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:38,400
Are you Chinese?

393
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:39,330
Exactly.

394
00:22:39,360 --> 00:22:40,920
You're just a watchdog.

395
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:42,970
What did you say?

396
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:44,480
Who are you calling a dog?

397
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:49,600
Watch out!

398
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:51,960
It's fine.

399
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:54,200
Who are you insulting?

400
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,120
I'm insulting you! What about it?

401
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:56,920
Get out of the way! Open the gate!

402
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,200
Open the gate!

403
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:05,800
Luggage.

404
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,320
Luggage.

405
00:23:08,080 --> 00:23:09,280
Slow down.

406
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:11,440
Grandpa, slow down.

407
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:12,120
Don't push.

408
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:12,840
Don't push.

409
00:23:13,560 --> 00:23:14,600
Step back.

410
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:16,610
Give them a warning.

411
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:21,440
You all saw that.

412
00:23:21,760 --> 00:23:22,880
I'll say it again.

413
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:25,920
Except for foreigners and those with passes,

414
00:23:26,080 --> 00:23:28,360
if anyone else dares to force their way in,

415
00:23:28,360 --> 00:23:29,640
they'll get a bullet.

416
00:23:29,960 --> 00:23:30,640
Protest!

417
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:31,640
Protest!

418
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:34,160
Concession!

419
00:23:35,360 --> 00:23:37,000
The magpie has a nest,

420
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:39,640
and the dove dwells in it.

421
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:42,280
This young lady is going to her new home.

422
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:43,640
Okay, sir.

423
00:23:43,840 --> 00:23:45,080
Even I can't understand it,

424
00:23:45,080 --> 00:23:45,960
let alone them.

425
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:47,040
Don't be mad at them.

426
00:23:47,040 --> 00:23:48,640
Slaves! Dogs!

427
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:49,400
Don't be mad at them.

428
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:49,960
Dogs!

429
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:51,240
Dogs! Slaves!

430
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:54,000
Step back!

431
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:55,520
Back up!

432
00:23:55,560 --> 00:23:56,320
Step back!

433
00:23:58,920 --> 00:24:00,250
National humiliation!

434
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:02,440
When will they let us in?

435
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:06,760
I heard they opened it for half an hour the day before yesterday.

436
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:08,440
Over a thousand people squeezed in.

437
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:10,480
Later, about ten people were killed,

438
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:11,810
and then they closed it.

439
00:24:12,040 --> 00:24:12,880
Miss,

440
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:15,600
I see there are many houses in this concession.

441
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:17,680
Their back doors all connect to Chinatown, right?

442
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:19,600
You think others didn't think of this?

443
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:20,640
The French said,

444
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:22,720
if anyone dares to let people in through the back door,

445
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:24,200
they will seal the whole house,

446
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,860
and kick the whole family out.

447
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:28,320
They're afraid people will take money and secretly let people in.

448
00:24:28,320 --> 00:24:28,960
Look,

449
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:32,120
all the doors on the street are nailed shut.

450
00:24:34,920 --> 00:24:35,760
Sir,

451
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:37,340
I think for the time being,

452
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:38,400
we can't get in.

453
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:40,920
Why don't we let Madam rest a bit?

454
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:41,800
Right.

455
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:43,680
Yujiao, take a rest.

456
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:46,800
Have a seat.

457
00:24:47,760 --> 00:24:48,360
Step back!

458
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:49,560
Stay away from the gate! Step back!

459
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:50,800
Step back!

460
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:53,600
Protest!

461
00:24:53,760 --> 00:24:55,620
Have something to eat first, sir.

462
00:24:56,040 --> 00:24:56,920
I won't eat.

463
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:01,800
Eat.

464
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:03,920
Eat well so we can fight them.

465
00:25:15,160 --> 00:25:16,920
Mom, I'm hungry.

466
00:25:28,840 --> 00:25:29,920
Thank you.

467
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:35,000
Slaves! Dogs!

468
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:37,360
Open the door!

469
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:39,600
Open the door!

470
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:45,530
You want to live, right?

471
00:25:46,080 --> 00:25:47,000
Four gold bars.

472
00:25:47,520 --> 00:25:48,880
You might as well just rob us.

473
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:49,920
What a jerk.

474
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:50,840
Then just wait.

475
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:52,570
Who do you think you are?

476
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:40,400
Look at this world.

477
00:26:41,040 --> 00:26:42,520
It's a living hell.

478
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:46,040
I can't stand seeing this.

479
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:49,920
Yes, I heard.

480
00:26:49,920 --> 00:26:52,240
They say you are a very capable person.

481
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:54,520
Bill, hello.

482
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:55,560
How are you?

483
00:26:55,760 --> 00:26:56,440
Hello, sir.

484
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:57,920
Good.

485
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:09,600
One person,

486
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:11,360
four bars.

487
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:17,720
Can you make it cheaper?

488
00:27:21,520 --> 00:27:22,960
Four bars it is.

489
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:47,680
Here are two.

490
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:50,720
A deposit.

491
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:01,920
Wait for me here at ten o'clock tonight.

492
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:03,000
Remember,

493
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:04,440
don't let anyone know.

494
00:28:04,440 --> 00:28:05,440
Okay.

495
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:07,000
Got it.

496
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:11,000
What will we do in the future?

497
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:12,760
Let's get into the Concession first.

498
00:28:12,760 --> 00:28:13,560
Hurry up.

499
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:23,800
An imported woolen coat.

500
00:28:24,720 --> 00:28:25,680
Looks nice.

501
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:27,240
Kid,

502
00:28:28,320 --> 00:28:29,800
you know your stuff.

503
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:31,800
What do you want?

504
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:34,760
What do I want?

505
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:36,720
It's what do you want.

506
00:28:38,120 --> 00:28:39,560
An inside job.

507
00:28:45,960 --> 00:28:48,360
If you want to keep my mouth shut,

508
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:49,760
it's easy.

509
00:28:50,160 --> 00:28:51,760
Tonight,

510
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:54,680
get four people inside for me.

511
00:28:57,560 --> 00:28:59,360
I won't let you do it for nothing.

512
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:01,480
I'll give you two gold bars.

513
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:05,200
Do you believe

514
00:29:05,760 --> 00:29:08,200
I'll report you to the French Municipal Council?

515
00:29:08,200 --> 00:29:09,920
Jean Paul from the Council

516
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:10,920
is my brother.

517
00:29:11,160 --> 00:29:13,120
We are sworn brothers.

518
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:15,080
Get out of here, you little brat!

519
00:29:16,480 --> 00:29:18,280
I'll report you to the Japanese.

520
00:29:24,280 --> 00:29:25,400
The Japanese?

521
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:27,240
The Japanese bullets

522
00:29:27,240 --> 00:29:28,520
have no eyes.

523
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:40,800
I'll shoot you, you little brat!

524
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:43,720
I am a living Buddha here.

525
00:29:44,120 --> 00:29:45,840
Look at that gate.

526
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:47,520
Every time it opens and closes,

527
00:29:47,520 --> 00:29:49,440
how many Chinese have I saved?

528
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:53,280
You little brat.

529
00:29:56,760 --> 00:29:57,280
Brother.

530
00:29:57,280 --> 00:29:58,520
No.

531
00:29:58,960 --> 00:30:00,080
Living Buddha.

532
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:00,480
Look,

533
00:30:00,480 --> 00:30:01,640
it's my fault.

534
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:03,800
I failed to recognize a great man.

535
00:30:04,360 --> 00:30:05,820
Are you going to report me?

536
00:30:05,960 --> 00:30:06,720
Me?

537
00:30:06,840 --> 00:30:07,920
What would I report?

538
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:09,880
I was blind.

539
00:30:11,920 --> 00:30:12,840
Brother, look.

540
00:30:14,080 --> 00:30:16,120
Zhang Renkui is my master.

541
00:30:16,280 --> 00:30:18,280
Please do me a favor for his sake.

542
00:30:18,920 --> 00:30:23,880
Shanghai Yuankui is your master?

543
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:26,560
We are both from Zaozhuang.

544
00:30:32,920 --> 00:30:33,920
Kid,

545
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:37,160
aren't you afraid of biting your tongue?

546
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:40,460
Living Buddha,

547
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:42,520
I am a refugee here.

548
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:43,120
Me,

549
00:30:44,120 --> 00:30:45,160
my father,

550
00:30:45,160 --> 00:30:46,520
my wife, and my nanny

551
00:30:46,520 --> 00:30:48,120
are all waiting there.

552
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:50,080
I really have no other choice.

553
00:30:50,080 --> 00:30:51,240
My business is gone.

554
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:53,080
My wife is pregnant.

555
00:30:53,080 --> 00:30:55,120
In this world, money is nothing.

556
00:30:55,120 --> 00:30:57,180
Only when you are alive is there hope.

557
00:30:58,040 --> 00:30:59,760
Brother, Living Buddha, I beg you.

558
00:30:59,760 --> 00:31:00,280
Tonight,

559
00:31:00,280 --> 00:31:01,960
get the four of us inside.

560
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:02,640
Please.

561
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:04,290
According to the rules.

562
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:06,360
It is what it is.

563
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:08,970
According to the rules.

564
00:31:10,440 --> 00:31:11,400
One person,

565
00:31:12,800 --> 00:31:13,760
four bars.

566
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:16,680
Not one less.

567
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:17,840
If you have the bars,

568
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:19,440
at 10:00 p.m.,

569
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:21,320
wait for me here.

570
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:09,160
Yueming,

571
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:10,920
when our family

572
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:13,440
was wandering in Shanghai,

573
00:32:13,960 --> 00:32:16,320
the Battle of Nanjing, 700 miles away,

574
00:32:16,320 --> 00:32:18,400
had reached its final moment.

575
00:32:19,400 --> 00:32:22,040
Due to the sheer disparity in strength between the enemy and us,

576
00:32:22,040 --> 00:32:24,720
the Nationalist Government's strategic decisions were seriously flawed

577
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:26,120
and wavering.

578
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:29,600
Furthermore, due to the extreme chaos in the command system,

579
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:31,360
the defense of Nanjing

580
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:33,280
collapsed rapidly.

581
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:12,680
Commander Liao sent me to let you go.

582
00:33:13,040 --> 00:33:14,480
What's the situation outside?

583
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:16,210
Zhonghua Gate is about to fall.

584
